This paper deals with memory consistency models in distributed systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of these models in operating systems (cs.OS) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also presents a theoretical framework for consistency models, which could be classified under the category of Architecture (cs.AR) or Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO).
